import React, { useEffect } from 'react'
import { useDispatch, useSelector } from 'react-redux'
import { viewProfile } from '../redux/authActions'

 const MyProfile = () => {
  const userId = useSelector( state => state.tokener._userId )
  const dispatch = useDispatch()
    useEffect(() => {
      dispatch(viewProfile(userId))
    },[userId])
    return(<>
      My Profile Page
      <Stack spacing={1} sx={{ maxWidth: 600 }}>
            <SnackbarContent message={movieName} action="User Name" />
            <SnackbarContent message={actorName} action="User Name"/>
            <SnackbarContent message={directorName} action=" Name" />
            <SnackbarContent message={description} action="Description" />
            <SnackbarContent message={startBookingDate} action="Release Date" />
            <SnackbarContent message={ticketCost} action="Ticket Cost" />
        </Stack>
    </>)
 }

 export default MyProfile
